{"iteration":8,"action":{"reasoning":"Observation: Iteration 7's 50-epoch natural-sampling model severely overfitted (train_acc ~100%, best val_bacc only 0.633) and its post-hoc logit adjustment scored 0.706, below the best 0.7275 from iteration 4. The smoke test also failed because predict.py looked for /data/test.pt which does not exist in the training container. Analysis: Standard CE with natural sampling quickly overfits to head classes; longer training hurts balanced accuracy. Instead of repeating the 15-epoch standard recipe, I will directly bake rebalancing into training with the Logit-Adjusted Loss (LA loss: CE on logits - log(priors))). This removes the prior bias during training so the model learns balanced representations naturally, allowing longer training without collapse. At test time on balanced data, raw logits should be used directly. Decision: Rewrite train.py with LA loss, 20 epochs, drop_path=0.1, and cosine LR. Run training, perform a local smoke test with a temporary fake test.pt, and submit eval immediately to measure the new baseline.","command":"python train.py --epochs 20 --drop_path 0.1 --la_tau 1.0 && mkdir -p /tmp/fake_test && cp /data/val.pt /tmp/fake_test/test.pt && python predict.py --data_path /tmp/fake_test --checkpoint checkpoints/best.pt --output /tmp/fake_test/out.json && head -c 200 /tmp/fake_test/out.json","submit_eval":{"checkpoint_path":"checkpoints/best.pt","predict_script":"predict.py"},"done":false,"files_written":["train.py"]},"command_output":{"exit_code":0,"timed_out":false,"elapsed_seconds":361.5595679283142,"stdout":"2026-04-29 10:41:52,259 WARNING: Epoch 1: train_loss=3.7220 train_acc=0.1424 train_bacc=0.0461 val_loss=5.8684 val_acc=0.1670 val_bacc=0.1670\n2026-04-29 10:41:52,594 WARNING: Saved best checkpoint with val_bacc=0.1670\n2026-04-29 10:42:08,090 WARNING: Epoch 2: train_loss=1.6359 train_acc=0.5745 train_bacc=0.2981 val_loss=3.9599 val_acc=0.3310 val_bacc=0.3310\n2026-04-29 10:42:08,433 WARNING: Saved best c